      "id": "8593c8b0-079f-4bf3-a279-dabe11f91c09",
      "name": "Read Sent for Dedup",
      "alwaysOutputData": true
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Collapse all 'Sent' rows into one item carrying:\n//  - the brief from Parse Brief (raw_brief, count, location, chat_id)\n//  - all_sent_emails: deduplicated lowercase array of every previously contacted email\n\nconst brief = $('Parse Brief').first().json;\nconst rows = $input.all();\nconst seen = new Set();\nfor (const r of rows) {\n  const e = (r.json?.email || '').toString().trim().toLowerCase();\n  if (e) seen.add(e);\n}\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    ...brief,\n    all_sent_emails: Array.from(seen)\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        208,
        -272
      ],
      "id": "65adec84-05bf-4a56-b105-0d80a3b43649",
      "name": "Aggregate Sent Emails"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Find {{ $json.count }} real, public businesses matching this brief: \"{{ $json.raw_brief }}\".\nLocation hint: {{ $json.location }}.\n\nReturn ONLY the JSON described in the system message. No markdown, no commentary.",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "=You are the **Lead Discovery Agent** for Arcom Technologies d.o.o. (a business-automation agency).\n\nYour ONLY job: find real, public businesses that match the user's brief and return a JSON object with a `leads` array. You do NOT write emails \u2014 that is a downstream agent's job. You need to decide niche/multiple niches that have the best potential for AI automation if it's not included.\n\nIf the brief only contains a number or does not specify a niche:\n- choose high-conversion niches from the preferred niches list\n- prefer businesses with publicly visible contact emails\n- continue normally\n- never return an empty array unless absolutely no valid businesses can be found\n\n# Workflow\n1. Use the web_search tool first. Do not rely on memory; search results may be stale.\n2. For each candidate business, locate a **public contact email** on:\n   - the company's own domain (e.g. info@business.hr, hello@business.com, contact@business.de),\n   - or a clearly listed booking/reservations/inquiries address.\n3. If you cannot confirm the email from a real public source (website, Google Business profile, official directory), **SKIP that business**. Find another. Never invent or guess an address.\n4. Capture one short, specific factual detail per business that we can use for personalisation (a unique service, a city, multiple locations, recent opening, certified specialty, etc.).\n\n# Target niches (prefer these \u2014 they buy automation):\nrestaurant \u00b7 cafe \u00b7 bakery \u00b7 hotel \u00b7 hostel \u00b7 dental clinic \u00b7 medical clinic \u00b7 beauty/hair salon \u00b7 spa \u00b7 gym \u00b7 accounting/tax firm \u00b7 finance/consulting boutique \u00b7 logistics/freight/warehouse \u00b7 recruitment/staffing/HR boutique \u00b7 ecommerce/retail brand \u00b7 construction/engineering firm with cost-estimate workflows.\n\n# Output schema (STRICT)\nReturn ONLY this JSON. No prose, no fences, no extra keys.\n\n{\n  \"leads\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Business Legal/Trade Name\",\n      \"website\": \"REDACTED_URL\",\n      \"country\": \"HR\",\n      \"city\": \"Zagreb\",\n      \"email\": \"info@example.com\",\n      \"niche\": \"dental\",\n      \"one_line_hook\": \"Three locations across Zagreb, focus on implants and prosthetics.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\nRules:\n- `country` is ISO-2 (HR, US, DE, IT, BA, RS, SI, ME, AT, FR, ...).\n- `niche` is lowercase, one of the categories above (or \"other\").\n- `email` MUST share the same root domain as `website` OR be a clearly listed public contact email (no Gmail/Yahoo unless that is genuinely on their site).\n- `one_line_hook` is in English, max 25 words, specific (no generic praise like \"great service\").\n- If you cannot find `count` valid leads, return as many as you can \u2014 do not pad with fakes.\n- Never include LinkedIn-only or guessed addresses."
        }
      },
